<H3> <TI>   Ciskei's Gqozo To Devote Energy to Electioneering </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2503112794 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1053 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2503112794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by E. Oelofse] </F>
  [Text] Bisho March 25 SAPA -- Former Ciskei ruler Brig Oupa 
Gqozo said on Friday [25 March] he could not have allowed a few 
unruly elements to create a Bophuthatswana-style debacle that 
would have stripped the Ciskeian people's dignity in the eyes of 
the world. 
  In an African Democratic Movement [ADM] statement, he 
explained the reasoning behind his resignation earlier this week 
after threats of violence and unrest in the homeland. Brig 
Gqozo said as leader of the ADM he would now be able to devote 
all his energy to winning seats in the election. "For me and my 
fellow candidates, it will be business as usual," he said. 

