<H3> <TI>   Alleged Third Force Informer Flees Country </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2503095394 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0648 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2503095394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg March 25 SAPA -- The policeman named as 
the mysterious Q who made disclosures about alleged third force 
violence -- Captain Kobus "Chappies" Klopper -- has apparently 
fled the country, SABC [South African Broadcasting Corporation] 
radio news reports. Two Johannesburg-based newspapers reported 
on Friday [25 March] morning the former Vlakplaas operative had 
gone into hiding, apparently in Europe. 
  One newspaper reported he left on a flight from Cape Town on 
Tuesday evening to Frankfurt, and then onto another destination 
in Europe. The report could not be confirmed. 
  News of his departure from the country comes amid a report 
in 
another newspaper that the Goldstone Commission has discovered a 
Swiss bank account used to fund third force activities. The 
newspaper said information about the fund was one of the cards 
Mr Justice Richard Goldstone was holding back as he prepared for 
an all out confrontation with Police Commissioner General Johan 
van der Merwe. 
  It said Judge Goldstone was also in possession of a 
video-tape incriminating several of the people named in its 
latest report. 

