<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Somalia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Faction Leaders Sign Reconciliation Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2403165394 Mogadishu Voice of the Somali Republic in 
Somali 1100 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2403165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mogadishu Voice of the Somali Republic </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Somali </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An official general agreement was signed today 
during the Somali reconciliation conference, which was attended 
by the leaders of the country's political organizations in 
Nairobi, Kenya. The ceremony marks the signing of the Somali 
reconciliation agreement, which took place at the Safari Park 
Hotel. The signing was witnessed by Ambassador Lansana Kouyate, 
the interim United Nations special envoy to Somalia, 
politicians, journalists, and distinguished guests from all 
parts of the world. 
  The UN-organized Somali national reconciliation conference 
had been in progress in Nairobi for a week before finally, at 
exactly 1300 East African time today, 24 March 1994, the 
agreement was signed by Ali Mahdi Mohamed, the president of the 
Somali Republic, who is also the representative of the Somali 
Salvation Alliance of 12 political organizations [SSA], and 
General Mohamed Farah Aidid, the representative of the Somali 
National Alliance [SNA]. 
  The agreement will be of great importance to the future of 
the Somali people. 
  During the signing ceremony, Ambassador Lansana Kouyate, Ali 
Mahdi Mohamed, and General Aidid delivered keynote speeches, all 
of them on the importance of the agreement for the future of the 
Somali people. We shall broadcast any further reports about the 
agreement to you in our later programs. 

</TEXT>

