<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Warns of War `At Any Time' With Nigeria </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2603093994 Paris Radio France International in French 0630 
GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2603093994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Cameroon Foreign Minister Ferdinand Oyono, 
currently in Addis Ababa for the OAU talks, has said that war 
between Cameroon and Nigeria can break out at any time over the 
Bakassi peninsula. He said he was not satisfied with the OAU 
recommendations which, despite urging troop withdrawal from the 
peninsula, have refrained from condemning the Abuja regime as 
Yaounde expected. According to Oyono, the Cameroon and Nigerian 
armies are now facing each other and are only 300 meters apart. 

</TEXT>

