Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg March 28 SAPA -- A spokesman for the 
SADF's [South African Defense Force] Witwatersrand Command said 
no army units had been called to Johannesburg's city centre to 
help contain violence surrounding the Zulu march in the central 
business district on Monday morning. Maj Christo Visser said 
soldiers were lending assistance to police in Soweto's 
Meadowlands where violence had apparently flared up on monday 
morning. 

