<H3> <TI>   Events Surrounding 28 Mar Zulu March Detailed </TI></H3>
<H4>   Four National Leaders To Meet 30, 31 Mar </H4>
<F P=102> MB2803172494 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1657 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2803172494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Patrick Bulger] </F>
  [Text] Pretoria March 28 SAPA -- President F W de Klerk, 
African National Congress President Nelson Mandela, Inkatha 
Freedom Party leader Mangosuthu Buthelezi and Zulu King Goodwill 
Zwelithini are to meet in an historic four-sided summit on 
Wednesday and Thursday. The meeting will be the first to bring 
together the four leaders at the centre of the unfolding 
political drama. 
  It is understood the chaos that racked central Johannesburg 
on Monday triggered the urgent attempt to bring the leaders 
together. 
  ANC Secretary General Cyril Ramaphosa and Minister of 
Constitutional Development Roelf Meyer left a scheduled 
Transitional Executive Council management committee meeting on 
Monday afternoon to join the IFP's Joe Matthews and the 
kwaZulu's Ben Ngubane for talks on the summit. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

