<H3> <TI>   Minister Stresses Need for Western Intervention </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903203594 Paris Radio France International in French 1830 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Burundi, the interior minister has called for the 
deployment of a buffer force of at least 5,000 men in his 
country. The minister has accused the Army of disobeying the 
government and of disarming Hutus only. He deems an 
intervention of Western countries as indispensable in Burundi. 

