<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNITA Radio Comments on Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2903204494 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 1900 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2903204494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The peace talks are continuing in Lusaka, Zambia. 
Today, the negotiating team of the National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola [UNITA] met with Faustino Muteka's 
delegation to study methods to be used in discussing the topic 
of dealing with the second round of presidential elections. The 
parties had to move to this topic because of the intransigence 
and arrogance demonstrated by the Popular Movement for the 
Liberation of Angola-Labor Party. Basing its arguments on the 
so-called electoral victory after the rigged elections, it 
refuses to make important concessions. Faced with an impasse, 
Alioune Blondin Beye, special representative of the UN secretary 
general in Angola, decided to move on to the electoral issue, 
which appears to be less polemical. 

</TEXT>

