<H3> <TI>   UNITA, Government Forces Clash in Malange </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB3003051994 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 1900 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB3003051994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] There was gunfire in Malange today. A military 
source said this happened when government troops tried to break 
through the defensive lines of the National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola [UNITA] in the region. The source also 
said that in the face of this provocation, the UNITA Armed 
Forces reacted with intense gunfire, forcing the enemy's 
immediate retreat. During the clashes, many government soldiers 
lost their lives. The situation is presently calm. 

</TEXT>

