<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNITA Reportedly Executes Security Firm Employee </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB3003053994 Johannesburg SAPA in English 2106 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB3003053994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria March 29 SAPA -- The UNITA [National Union 
for the Total Independence of Angola] rebel movement executed an 
Executive Outcome employee who had been captured while providing 
training and security in Angola, the company said in a statement 
on Tuesday. The company gave the man's name as Steyn Marais. 
  Pretoria-based Executive Outcome hires "security guards" to 
protect Angolan Government installations. 
  Through its attorneys, the company said information from 
Angolan sources said two other Executive Outcome employees had 
been wounded and UNITA was denying them outside medical 
attention. The men were captured last Thursday [24 March]. 
  An attorney said their names and details of where they had 
been captured and were being held would not be released at this 
stage. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-1502 </DOCNO>
