<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Mozambique </F>
<H3> <TI>   Unomoz Reports 6,356 Soldiers Demobilized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB3003055394 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1900 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB3003055394 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A total of 46 government and three Mozambique 
National Resistance [Renamo] soldiers presented themselves in 
assembly areas throughout the country 28 March. A total of 
48,155 soldiers had presented themselves in assembly areas by 28 
March, 23,347 from the government and 14,808 from Renamo. The 
UN Operations in Mozambique [Unomoz] daily report says that by 
28 March 6,356 soldiers from both sides were demobilized, 6,150 
from the government and 206 from Renamo. 

</TEXT>

