<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Issue Statement on Johannesburg Violence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2903170694 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1638 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2903170694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg March 29 SAPA -- At least 53 people 
died as a result of violence that flared in Johannesburg on 
Monday [28 March], police said on Tuesday. A police statement 
said an investigation into the killings had begun under the 
leadership of Brig Louis van der Westhuizen. The police said 
permission for the Zulu meeting had been applied for and 
granted; the meeting had been peaceful until shooting started; 
chaos and violence followed when "groups of persons" at the 
meeting proceeded into different parts of the city; and one of 
these groups proceeded to African National Congress headquarters 
at Shell House. "Shooting with automatic weapons from within 
Shell House left eight persons dead and 20 persons injured," the 
statement said. "No automatic firearms were found among the 
dead or injured outside Shell House. Two handguns, one of which 
was homemade, were found among these persons." 

</TEXT>

