<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   IEC Investigating Voter Card Irregularities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB3003094694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB3003094694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Independent Electoral Commission [IEC] has begun 
an investigation into reports of people under the age of 18 
years being in possession of temporary voter cards. The IEC 
said the irregularities had allegedly occurred in Natal. Two 
Scotland Yard officers are assisting in the investigation. The 
IEC said steps had been taken, in cooperation with the 
Department of Home Affairs, to tighten procedures for obtaining 
temporary voter cards. It said that possible strategies were 
being investigated to filter out underage holders of temporary 
voter cards before the elections. 

</TEXT>

