<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   TEC Proposes Locations for Provincial Legislatures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB3003053594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 2033 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB3003053594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by S Denny] </F>
  [Text] Pretoria March 29 SAPA--The Transitional Executive 
Council [TEC] has proposed the cities and towns where the nine 
provincial legislatures could convene within seven days of the 
elections, SABC radio news reported on Tuesday. It said in 
Pretoria, however, these centres would not necessarily be the 
provincial capitals. 
  The cities are: Cape Town for the Western Cape; Johannesburg 
for the PWV [Pretoria, Witwatersrand, Vereeniging] region; 
Bloemfontein for the [Orange] Free State; Mmabatho for the North 
West Region; Kimberley for the Northern Cape; Pietermaritzburg 
for kwaZulu/Natal; and Nelspruit for the Eastern Transvaal. 
  It suggested both King William's Town and Bisho for the 
Eastern Cape and both Pietersburg and Lebowakgomo for the 
Northern Transvaal. 

</TEXT>

