<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alleged ANC Officials Arrested in Port Shepstone </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB3003094594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0910 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB3003094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Port Shepstone March 30 SAPA -- Four suspects were 
arrested for illegal possession of several firearms and 
ammunition in Port Shepstone on the Natal lower South Coast on 
Tuesday [29 March], Durban police spokesman Maj Bala Naidoo 
said. The suspects are believed to be African National Congress 
[ANC] officials. 
  A ANC peace desk official confirmed the arrests, adding he 
had "no clue" as to why they were detained. 
  Maj Naidoo said a vehicle was stopped in Port Shepstone on 
Tuesday morning and police recovered an AK-47 rifle and 
magazine, 20 AK-47 rounds, and a 9mm Luger pistol with rounds. 
  "The local offices of a political party", were subsequently 
searched and a 9mm CZ pistol and a police camoflauge cap were 
found, said Maj Naidoo. The men are due in court soon. 

</TEXT>

