<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister Calls For International Force </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3003140694 Paris Radio France International in French 1230 
GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3003140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Security in Burundi: The Interior Minister 
Leonard Nyangoma, currently in Brussels, has sounded the alarm. 
He has asked the international community to send a 5,000-man 
buffer force to his country to put an end to inter-ethnic 
clashes. Leonard Nyangoma was interviewed by Anne-Marie 
Mouradian: 
  [Begin Nyangoma recording] The mission of this force would 
be 
to guarantee the security of institutions and the population. 
It could also contribute to the reorganization of the national 
army, because our army is no longer capable of guaranteeing the 
security of institutions and the population today. I do not 
think the OAU can undertake such an operation on its own. The 
West has come to the aid of Uganda, Somalia, and Sarajevo, why 
shouldn't it do the same for Burundi? [end recording] [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

