<H3> <TI>   Bongo's Daughter Appointed Undersecretary </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB3003133394 Paris AFP in French 0937 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB3003133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Libreville, 26 Mar (AFP) -- On 26 March, official 
sources disclosed that Mrs. Pascaline Mferri Bongo, President 
Omar Bongo's daughter and former Gabonese foreign minister, was 
appointed permanent undersecretary to the Presidency in charge 
of francophone affairs by presidential decree on 25 March. 
  Mrs. Mferri Bongo joined the government in June 1991, when 
she took over the post held by Ali Bongo, another one of 
President Omar Bongo's children. 
  In the cabinet formed by Prime Minister Casimir Oye-Mba on 
25 
March, former Mines Minister Jean Ping became the new foreign 
minister. However, the title of his post is simply "minister of 
foreign affairs and cooperation," while that of Mrs. Mferri 
Bongo used to be "minister of foreign affairs, cooperation, and 
francophone affairs." 

</TEXT>

