Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] on 28 March, UNITA [National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola] armed forces repelled yet another 
attempt by Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola-Labor 
Party troops to occupy Amboiva, a UNITA-controlled area 
southeast of Vila Nova do Seles. The commune was defended 
during clashes that went on throughout the night. The enemy 
suffered heavy human and material losses. Our correspondent in 
the area reports: 
  War materiel captured by UNITA includes one RPG-7, one 60-mm 
mortar, thousands of rounds of ammunition, and hundreds of 
shells. The enemy, which abandoned 21 People's Armed Forces for 
the Liberation of Angola soldiers killed, fled in disarray. 

