<H3> <TI>   Iranian Foreign Minister Concludes Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3003133394 Tehran IRNA in English 1311 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3003133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Conakry, March 30, IRNA -- Foreign Minister of Iran 
'Ali Akbar Velayati left here for Burkina Faso today at the end 
of his two-day visit and was seen off at the airport by his 
Guinean counterpart Ibrahima Sylla Wednesday [30 March]. 
  During his stay here, Velayati conferred with Guinean 
President Lansana Conte, and conveyed to him a message from 
President 'Ali Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani. Velayati, who arrived 
here Tuesday after a stopover in Chad, also held talks with 
Sylla and Guinean Minister of Natural Resources Toumani Dakoum 
Sako. He also attended a large gathering of Guinean Muslims at 
the Jame' Mosque in Conakry where he called for expansion of 
bilateral ties in all grounds. 
  Waving the flags of the Islamic Republic of Iran and 
carrying 
pictures of the father of the Islamic revolution, the late Imam 
Khomeyni, and the present leader of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
'Ali Khamene'i, Guinean Muslims in Conakry warmly welcomed the 
Iranian delegation. 
  Velayati is to visit Burkina Faso on the second leg of his 
six-nation tour of African states which will also take him to 
Zimbabwe, Uganda, Kenya and Namibia. 

</TEXT>

