<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Thai Minister Meets Qian, Says One-China Policy in Effect </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2702214394 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1554 
GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2702214394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bangkok, 27 Feb (XINHUA) -- Qian Qichen, Chinese 
vice premier and foreign minister, during a short stopover here 
today on route to Sri Lanka from Bangladesh met with Thai 
Foreign Minister Prasong Sunsiri. The two exchanged views on 
issues of common concern. 
  Prasong reiterated that Thailand will abide by the 
principles 
laid down in the communique on the establishment of diplomatic 
relation between Thailand and China and will follow the 
one-China policy. 
  He emphasized that his country treasures the relations of 
friendship and cooperation between the two country forged in the 
past 19 years since diplomatic relations were established and 
that it will make efforts not to hurt such relations. 
  Qian Qichen will leave here tomorrow for a visit to Sri 
Lanka. 

</TEXT>

