<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Reports on Leaders' Lantern Festival Party </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2502201594 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1542 
GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2502201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By RENMIN RIBAO reporter Chen Weiwei (7115 4850 0251) and </F>
XINHUA reporter Zou Aiguo (6760 1947 0948)] 
  [Text] Beijing, 24 Feb (XINHUA) -- On Lantern Festival 
night, the Great Hall of the People was decorated with colorful 
lanterns and was filled with good cheer and laughter. Jiang 
Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Li Ruihuan, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao, 
Rong Yiren, and other leading comrades, as well as more than 200 
prominent figures from Beijing's intellectual circles, joyfully 
gathered at the Eastern Main Hall to celebrate the jubilant 
occasion. 
  The Eastern Main Hall was graced by red lanterns, was 
permeated with the fragrance of narcissus, and was filled with a 
jubilant atmosphere. Jiang Zemin, other comrades, and prominent 
figures from the capital's literary, art, science and 
technology, education, theoretical, and journalistic circles -- 
who were seated around round tables -- exchanged Spring Festival 
greetings while enjoying fine tea and chatting cheerfully. 
  Amid the smiling faces, Hu Jintao stepped up to the podium 
and, on behalf of the CPC Central Committee, extended his 
festival greetings and cordial regards to the comrades and 
friends in the hall and to comrades and friends of the country's 
intellectual circles. He thanked everyone for making 
outstanding contributions to the country's reform, opening up, 
and socialist modernization. 
  Hu Jintao said that he hoped everyone, under the guidance of 
Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with 
Chinese characteristics and under the leadership of the CPC 
Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin as its core, would 
further unite and work even harder to take a new step forward, 
score new achievements, and make new contributions to the 
development of socialist literature, arts, sciences, technology, 
education, theories, and journalism. He expressed his hope that 
the great motherland will become more dynamic and prosperous, 
wealthier, and stronger. 
  The soiree was preceded by the song "The Moon of the 15th of 
the Month." Artists attending the soiree performed vocal solos, 
instrumental solos, instrumental ensembles, Beijing opera songs, 
vocal duets, and a magic show, winning sustained applause. 
  Jiang Zemin and other comrades, while viewing the 
performances, chatted with scientists, educators, and artists at 
their respective tables, and cordially inquired about their work 
and lives. While listening to the pipa [Chinese musical 
instrument] solo "The Lantern and the Moon Shine on Each Other," 
Jiang Zemin said, "The pipa is our national art; we should 
promote our national arts." While the "Song of the Guerrillas" 
was being played, Jiang Zemin said, "This is an immortal work." 
  The one hour, 40-minute soiree ended amid the song "Singing 
the Motherland." Hu Jintao wished everyone a happy Spring 
Festival, good health, family happiness, and a successful career. 
  Leading comrades also attending the soiree, included Li 
Lanqing, Li Tieying, Wen Jiabao, Lei Jieqiong, Wang Guangying, 
Buhe, Song Jian, Luo Gan, Wang Zhaoguo, Zhao Puchu, Hu Sheng, 
and Qian Zhengying. 

</TEXT>

