<F P=102>  OW2802083094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0807 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2802083094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 28 (XINHUA) -- Aisin Giorro Pu 
Jie, brother of the last Chinese Emperor Aisin Giorro Puyi, died 
of illness at 7:55 am [2355 GMT 27 February] today, at the age 
of 87. 
  Pu Jie was a member of the Standing Committee of the Eighth 
National People's Congress (NPC), vice-chairman of the NPC 
Nationalities Committee, and a commissioner of the Subcommittee 
of Cultural and Historical Data of the National Committee of the 
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC). 

