<H3> <TI>   Satellite Named For Local Refrigerator Company </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2702124794 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1542 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2702124794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By correspondent Liu Linzong (0491 2651 1350) and reporter </F>
Li Xiuqing (2621 4423 3237)] 
  [Text] Beijing, 25 Feb (XINHUA) -- The simulated satellite 
successfully launched into space by the carrier rocket "Long 
March 3-A" on 8 February was officially named the "Star of the 
Hualing Group" at the China Institute of Carrier Rocket 
Technology today. It was the first time in our country's 
aerospace history that a man-made earth satellite was named 
after an enterprise. 
  Guangzhou's Hualing Limited Company Group mainly produces 
Hualing-brand refrigerators and other household electrical 
appliances, and is one of "the country's top 10 enterprises that 
produce household electrical appliances." To support our 
country's aerospace service, the company donated 500,000 yuan to 
the aerospace industry before the "Long March 3-A" rocket was 
launched. To express its gratitude, the rocket technology 
institute painted the Hualing group's business emblem on the 
satellite's cowling and placed inside the satellite a model of 
the national gold medal awarded to the company. 

</TEXT>

