<H3> <TI>   `Small Calibre' Satellite Earth Station Set Up </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2302100294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0903 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2302100294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, February 23 (XINHUA) -- The main station 
of a satellite ground station of a very small calibre started 
operation yesterday in East China's Shanghai. 
  The station will be able to provide satellite channels, 
connect any other ground station of a very small calibre in 
China and international satellite channels. 
  Customers will be able to enter the main station at any 
point 
in Shanghai and set up data communications channels with any 
other user in China. 
  Shanghai Petroleum Exchange has become the first user of the 
station. 
  The satellite ground station system with a very small 
calibre 
sprung into being in the 1980s and their construction costs half 
that of ground stations in popular use now. 
  There are now more than 100,000 such systems in the world. 

</TEXT>

