<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Publications Network Established </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2402184094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1259 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2402184094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 24 (XINHUA) -- China's first 
computer-equipped national information network center on books, 
newspapers and magazines has been set up in Beijing. 
  The network of 50 advanced computers can provide instant 
indexing services for its 260,000 customers nationwide. 
  The data input center of the network is located in Ningbo in 
east China and employs 500 operators who can input 7.5 million 
Chinese characters each day. 
  Summaries and titles of books, newspapers and magazines 
newly-published in the country can be immediately input into the 
computer system. 
  In order to promote its business, the center will present 
4,000 computers to its major customers in education and service 
sectors. 
  The center was jointly set up by companies in Beijing and 
Ningbo in Zhejiang Province. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

