<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Views Qian Qichen's Bangladesh Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Justice Minister Hosts Banquet </H4>
<F P=102> OW2502180294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1654 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2502180294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dhaka, February 25 (XINHUA) -- Bangladesh people are 
conscious of the importance of China's role in the United 
Nations and other international organizations. 
  As a permanent member of the U.N. Security Council, China 
shares a great responsibility for the successful realization of 
the ideals and objectives of the United Nations. 
  Mr. Mirza Golam Hafiz, Bangladesh minister for law, justice 
and parliamentary affairs and president of the Bangladesh-China 
Friendship Association made the remarks when hosting a welcoming 
banquet on Friday [25 February] evening on behalf of the 
association for the visiting Chinese Vice Premier Qian Qichen. 
  Qian, who is also foreign minister of China, thanked Mr. 
Hafiz and other members of the Bangladesh-China Friendship 
Association for their ceaseless efforts in promoting 
understanding, friendship and cooperation between the two 
peoples. 
  The Chinese vice premier described the Sino-Bangladesh 
friendship as "time-tested" and he believed the friendship will 
be further strengthened and developed through the efforts of the 
two sides. 
  Qian, who flew here from Pakistan on Thursday, is on a 
four-day official goodwill visit to Bangladesh, the second leg 
of his five-nation tour also including Sri Lanka, Maldives and 
Iran. 
  On Friday afternoon, Qian paid a visit to the No. One 
Bangladesh-China Friendship Bridge which was constructed by a 
Chinese firm and is so far the longest of its kind in the 
country. 

</TEXT>

