<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Views Qian Qichen's Bangladesh Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets Prime Minister </H4>
<F P=102> OW2602171394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1239 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2602171394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dhaka, February 26 (XINHUA) -- Prime Minister 
Khaleda Zia said here today that China's economy has been 
rapidly developing in recent years due to its reform and 
open-door policy and Bangladesh hopes to learn from China's 
experience for its own economic development. 
  Talking to visiting Chinese Deputy Premier and Foreign 
Minister Qian Qichen, who called on her at her office this 
afternoon, Khaleda Zia said that the present Government of 
Bangladesh attached great importance to the development of 
friendly cooperation between Bangladesh and China and hopes to 
further strengthen their bilateral cooperation. 
  Qian Qichen expressed his satisfaction with the development 
of the traditional friendship between the two countries in 
recent years, saying that the Chinese Government highly valued 
the friendly cooperation between the two countries. 
  Khaleda Zia briefed the Chinese foreign minister on the 
cooperation among member states of the South Asian Alliance [as 
received] for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) founded on the 
initiative of the late President Ziaur Rahman, and sought 
China's support for the SAARC. 
  Qian Qichen said China hopes that SAARC would play an active 
role in economic developments of SAARC member states as well as 
in resolving the existing disputes among the SAARC states. 
  Qian Qichen today also called on President Abdur Rahman 
Biswas at the president's office. 
  Abdur Rahman Biswas spoke highly of China's rapid economic 
development and expressed the hope that the economic cooperation 
between China and Bangladesh will be further strengthened. 
  Qian Qichen said both China and Bangladesh are now 
concentrating their efforts on economic development for raising 
the living standard of their people. The two countries should 
support each other and strengthen their cooperation, he added. 
  He said the Chinese Government will encourage Chinese 
companies and enterprises to invest in Bangladesh. 

</TEXT>

