GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2702054794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Pan Xiaozhu (3382 1420 3796)] </F>
  [Text] Dhaka, 26 Feb (XINHUA) -- Qian Qichen, vice premier 
of China's State Council and concurrently foreign minister, 
called on Bangladesh Prime Minister Khaleda Zia at the 
Bangladesh prime minister office this afternoon. They expressed 
their satisfaction at the smooth development of friendly and 
cooperative relations between the two countries. 
  Zia stated: The Bangladesh Government attaches importance to 
developing friendly and cooperative relations with China, and 
the Bangladesh people thank China for the aid provided to them. 
  Zia said she was pleased to note the progress and rapid 
economic development China achieved in reform and opening up in 
recent years. She added: "Bangladesh hopes to draw on China's 
experience in economic reform for its own economic development 
process, and to further strengthen friendly and cooperative 
relations between the two nations." 
  Qian Qichen responded: There is a long history of 
Sino-Bangladesh friendship, and there has been new developments 
in relations between the two nations in recent years. China is 
satisfied with these relations. The Chinese Government has 
consistently attached importance to developing friendly and 
cooperative relations with Bangladesh. Qian Qichen said he held 
very good talks with Foreign Minister Rahman during the current 
visit. He believed the visit would definitely further promote 
comprehensive development of friendly and cooperative relations 
between the two nations in various fields. 
  Qian Qichen congratulated Prime Minister Zia on Bangladesh's 
steady development under her leadership. 
  Zia gave a briefing on South Asian regional cooperation, 
expressing her hope that China would support such cooperation. 
Qian Qichen said: Regional cooperation was initiated by the 
late Bangladesh President Ziaur Rahman. China is pleased to see 
new development in South Asian regional cooperation in recent 
years. China hopes the South Asian Association for Regional 
Cooperation will play an active role in solving South Asian 
problems in economic development as well as problems existing 
among these nations. 
  Qian Qichen conveyed Premier Li Peng's regards to Prime 
Minister Zia and extended Li Peng's invitation to visit China. 
Zia gladly accepted the invitation and asked Qian Qichen to 
convey to Premier Li Peng her greetings and invitation to visit 
Bangladesh. 

</TEXT>

