<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Organs To Help Shift to Market Economy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2702135694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1336 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2702135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nanjing, February 27 (XINHUA) -- A working 
conference on organizational work of the Communist Party of 
China (CPC) held last week called on party committees at all 
levels to make investigations and strengthen macro-guidance to 
help a smooth shift to the market economy. 
  Lu Feng and Zhao Zongnai, the head and deputy head of the 
Organizational Department of the Central Committee of CPC 
addressed the conference, which was held in Wuxi in East China's 
Jiangsu Province. 
  The conference, sponsored by the CPC Organizational 
Department, was convened to explore effective solutions in 
organizational work for problems appearing in the current reform 
drive, so as to guarantee the country's economic development and 
social ability. 
  Lu said that leading bodies should have a clear 
understanding 
of their roles under present conditions and should further 
emancipate the mind to deepen the reform of the personnel system. 
  He stressed that making investigations and studying and 
strengthening macro-guidance are fundamental to enhancing 
efficiency and improving work-style in the field. 
  Lu urged leading officials to be bold in carrying out reform 
and to be realistic in conducting investigations and study in 
order to find practical solutions. He also urged them to put 
stress on problems waiting for immediate resolution. 
  In his speech, Zhao hoped that leading bodies will transform 
the findings from investigations and study into regulations, 
rules and concrete measures. 
  He reaffirmed that the main task in the field is to offer an 
organizational guarantee for the establishment of the 
market-oriented economy. 
  At the conference, delegates from ten provinces and cities, 
such as Jiangsu, Shanghai and Beijing, introduced their work 
experience. And the conference participants also set new tasks 
for themselves there. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

