<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Joint-Stock Businesses Increase Throughout Nation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2802092694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0807 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2802092694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 28 (XINHUA) -- China has seen good 
progress in the implementation of the joint-stock system. 
  So far, over 13,000 enterprises have adopted the new system, 
with more than 208.6 billion yuan in stock capital and some 25 
million shareholders. 
  Statistics show that these firms are located in 30 
provinces, 
autonomous regions and municipalities in the country. The three 
provinces of Shandong, Zhejiang and Sichuan have over 800 such 
companies each, and Henan, Hubei and Jiangsu Provinces have more 
than 600 each. The Tibet Autonomous Region has set up four such 
enterprises, with a total stock capital of 200 million yuan. 
  So far, 122 shareholding companies have floated stocks on 
the 
market, mostly in the cities of Beijing, Shanghai and Tianjin, 
and the provinces of Liaoning, Jiangsu and Guangdong. 

</TEXT>

