<H3> <TI>   Jiangsu People's Congress Holds Preparatory Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2702180694 Nanjing Jiangsu People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2702180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nanjing Jiangsu People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News" program] </F>
  [Text] Preparations for convening the Second Session of the 
Eighth Jiangsu Provincial People's Congress have been completed. 
A preparatory meeting was held at the Great Hall of the People 
in Nanjing yesterday afternoon. The meeting was presided over 
by Zhang Yaohua, deputy chairman of the provincial people's 
congress Standing Committee. He announced that there were 985 
deputies to the provincial people's congress and that 875 
deputies attended the meeting yesterday, thus forming a quorum. 
  The preparatory meeting, by adopting the method of counting 
raised hands, elected the presidium and secretary general of the 
second session of the eighth provincial people's congress. The 
presidium is composed of 73 people, with Zhang Yaohua serving as 
its secretary general. 
  The preparatory meeting adopted the agenda for the second 
session: hearing and deliberating the work report of the 
provincial people's government; examining and approving the 
implementation of Jiangsu's economic and social development plan 
for 1993 and its economic and social development for 1994; 
examining and approving the implementation of Jiangsu's budget 
for 1993 and its 1994 budget; hearing and deliberating the work 
report of the provincial people's congress standing committee; 
hearing and deliberating the work report of the provincial 
people's procuratorate; and electing the chief procurator of the 
provincial people's procuratorate. 
  Shen Daren, Gao Dezheng, Zhang Yaohua, Ling Qihong, Wu 
Xijun, 
and Qu Qinyue were seated at the rostrum. 

</TEXT>

