<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shandong Urges People To Guard Political Stability </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2702041194 Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2702041194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 26 February at the forum cosponsored by the 
provincial party committee and the provincial government, Li 
Wenquan, deputy secretary of the provincial party committee, set 
forth that the party organizations at various levels, the party- 
member cadres, and the broad masses of the people across the 
province should go all out to safeguard political and social 
stability and ensure the smooth progress of reform, opening up, 
and modernization. 
  Li Wenquan said in his speech: In the preceding stage, the 
province had a situation characterized by political stability, 
social stability, economic development, and market prosperity, 
and in which the people lived and worked in peace and 
contentment. However, we must notice that there are still 
factors affecting social and political stability and the tasks 
for keeping stability are still arduous. The party and 
government leading comrades at various levels should approach 
from the high plane of the overall situation and from the high 
political plane to grasp and well handle the relationship among 
reform, development, and stability; go all out to safeguard the 
stability of the overall situation; and never, in the slightest 
degree, be vague on or shake this matter of principle. At 
present, we should emphatically grasp the basic work of the 
grass roots, the improvement of administrative honesty, the 
improvement of ideology and work style, and the setup of legal 
system to ensure and promote the smooth progress of reform, 
opening up, and modernization. 
  Sun Shuyi, standing committee member of the provincial party 
committee and secretary of the provincial commission of 
political science and law; and Wang Yuxi, vice governor of the 
provincial government, attended and addressed the forum. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
